    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Brugmann University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Arterial pulse pressure variation induced by mechanical ventilation (ΔPP) is considered one
      of the best parameter to predict fluid responsiveness in patients under general anaesthesia.
      Pleth Variability Index (PVI) has been proposed as a less invasive alternative. However, the
      pneumoperitoneum has been recently seen suggested as a limitation to their interpretation.
      The aim of this observational study is to compare changes in ΔPP and PVI related to
      autotransfusion associated with a Trendelenburg manoeuver before and during laparoscopy in
      patients undergoing elective surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
